hey succeed by their </div><div class="t mb6d x26 h32 y330 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">own strength, </div><div class="t ma53 x27 h32 y61f ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but their way of thinking I can&apos;t </div><div class="t m24d x26 h32 y652 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accept&quot; (Job 21:14-16, TEV). </div><div class="t m2bc xb9 h35 y4fb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The third dialogue or cycle, as </div><div class="t maf1 xd0 h35 y60d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">,understood by the author of these </div><div class="t m10a xd4 h35 y857 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lessons, includes Job 21 through 31. </div><div class="t m816 xd4 h35 y197 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">These chapters cover the following </div><div class="t m588 xd4 h35 yaf ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">items: </div><div class="t m702 xb9 h35 y1cf ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;1. Job&apos;s first speech: he maintains </div><div class="t m731 x26 h35 y124 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that the wicked sometimes </div><div class="t m217 x26 h35 y3bb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">prosper, 21:1-34. </div><div class="t m7d6 xe h35 y584 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m51 x26 h35 y584 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz&apos;s speech: he urges Job </div><div class="t m110 x26 h35 y58 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to repent, 22:1-30. </div><div class="t m210 xe h35 y6a2 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m586 x26 h35 y6a2 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s second speech: he </div><div class="t m335 x26 h35 y265 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expresses his longing for an </div><div class="t m12f4 x26 h35 y9cf ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">opportunity to appear before </div><div class="t m8c5 x27 h35 yb9 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">, God, 23:1 to 24:25. </div><div class="t ma7c xe h35 y5fb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m227 x26 h35 yb03 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bildad&apos;s speech: he asserts that </div><div class="t m7a2 x26 h35 y106 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">man cannot be justified before </div><div class="t me0 x18 h35 